---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CourseStyles from '../../components/CourseStyles.astro';
---

<Layout title="Python Intermediate Course - Coding with Eric">
	<CourseStyles />
	<main class="course-main">
		<h1 class="course-title">Python <span class="text-gradient">Intermediate</span></h1>
		<div class="course-content">
			<h2 class="course-subtitle">10-Week Advanced Python Course Outline</h2>
			
			<div class="week-grid">
				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 1: Review of Python Basics and Course Goals</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Quick review of key basic concepts: loops, functions, and data types</li>
						<li>Introduction to course structure and expectations</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Revise and enhance a previous project (e.g., Guess the Number)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 2: File Handling</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Reading from and writing to files</li>
						<li>Working with text and CSV files</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Create a simple diary or note-taking application</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 3: Error Handling and Debugging</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Common Python errors and how to fix them</li>
						<li>Using try, except, finally for error handling</li>
						<li>Debugging tips and tools</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Build a program with intentional errors and debug it</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 4: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) Basics</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Introduction to classes and objects</li>
						<li>Attributes, methods, and the self keyword</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Create a class-based animal or character simulator</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 5: Advanced OOP Concepts</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Inheritance, polymorphism, and encapsulation</li>
						<li>Magic methods (__init__, __str__, etc.)</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Build a class hierarchy for a game (e.g., players, enemies)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 6: Working with Modules and Libraries</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>What are modules and libraries?</li>
						<li>Installing and using third-party libraries (pip)</li>
						<li>Introduction to popular Python libraries: math, random, datetime</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Build a random password generator or calendar program</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 7: Introduction to Data Structures and Algorithms</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Lists, tuples, sets, and dictionaries in depth</li>
						<li>Sorting and searching algorithms (e.g., bubble sort)</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Create a leaderboard system for a game</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 8: Simple Data Visualization</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Introduction to the matplotlib library</li>
						<li>Creating basic charts (line, bar, pie)</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Visualize data from a simple quiz or survey</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 9: Advanced Game Development Concepts</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Using the pygame library for graphical games</li>
						<li>Adding images, sounds, and controls to games</li>
						<li>Mini-project: Build a basic interactive game (e.g., a maze or pong game)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="week-card">
					<h3>Week 10: Capstone Project</h3>
					<ul class="course-list">
						<li>Plan, design, and develop a complete project from start to finish</li>
						<li>Example projects:
							<ul class="course-list-nested">
								<li>A text-based RPG</li>
								<li>A simple graphical game using pygame</li>
								<li>A basic personal finance tracker</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
						<li>Present projects to the class and celebrate achievements!</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>